headline: CDNS Q3 Deep Dive: AI Demand and Hardware Momentum Offset Cautious Market Reaction
summary: Electronic design automation company Cadence Design Systems (NASDAQ:CDNS) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 10.1% year on year to $1.34 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.93 per share was 7.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
